#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:5
msgid "Embind"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:7
msgid ""
"*Embind* is used to bind C++ functions and classes to JavaScript, so that "
"the compiled code can be used in a natural way by \"normal\" JavaScript. "
"*Embind* also supports :ref:`calling JavaScript classes from C++ <embind-val-"
"guide>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:12
msgid ""
"Embind has support for binding most C++ constructs, including those "
"introduced in C++11 and C++14. Its only significant limitation is that it "
"does not currently support :ref:`raw pointers with complicated lifetime "
"semantics <embind-raw-pointers>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:17
msgid ""
"This article shows how to use :cpp:func:`EMSCRIPTEN_BINDINGS` blocks to "
"create bindings for functions, classes, value types, pointers (including "
"both raw and smart pointers), enums, and constants, and how to create "
"bindings for abstract classes that can be overridden in JavaScript. It also "
"briefly explains how to manage the memory of C++ object handles passed to "
"JavaScript."
msgstr ""

