#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:244
msgid "Automatic memory management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:246
msgid "Embind integrates with the `Explicit Resource Management`_ proposal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:248
msgid ""
"It allows to automatically delete short-lived C++ objects at the end of the "
"scope when they're declared with a `using` keyword:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:256
msgid ""
"At the moment of writing, this proposal is natively supported in Chromium-"
"based browsers as well as Babel and TypeScript via transpilation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:259
msgid ""
"Embind also supports `finalizers`_, which were added in ECMAScript 2021 "
"under a `FinalizationRegistry`_ API. Unlike the `using` keyword, finalizers "
"are not guaranteed to be called, and even if they are, there are no "
"guarantees about their timing or order of execution, which makes them "
"unsuitable for general RAII-style resource management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:265
msgid ""
"Embind uses it for cleanup if available, but only for smart pointers, and "
"only as a last resort."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:268
msgid ""
"It is strongly recommended that JavaScript code explicitly deletes any C++ "
"object handles it has received."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:273
msgid "Cloning and Reference Counting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:275
msgid ""
"There are situations in which multiple long-lived portions of the JavaScript "
"codebase need to hold on to the same C++ object for different amounts of "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:279
msgid ""
"To accommodate that use case, Emscripten provides a `reference counting`_ "
"mechanism in which multiple handles can be produced for the same underlying "
"C++ object. Only when all handles have been deleted does the object get "
"destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:284
