#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1299
msgid "Custom ``val`` Definitions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1301
msgid ""
":cpp:class:`emscripten::val` types are mapped to TypeScript's `any` type by "
"default, which does not provide much useful information for API's that "
"consume or produce `val` types. To give better type information, custom "
"`val` types can be registered using :cpp:func:`EMSCRIPTEN_DECLARE_VAL_TYPE` "
"in combination with :cpp:class:`emscripten::register_type`. An example below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1307
msgid "Two registration forms are supported:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1309
msgid ""
"Single parameter: ``register_type<T>(definition)`` — the provided string is "
"inlined"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1310
msgid "everywhere the type appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1311
msgid ""
"Two parameters: ``register_type<T>(name, definition)`` — creates a named "
"TypeScript"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1312
msgid ""
"type alias (``type name = definition;``) and uses ``name`` at call sites."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1333
msgid "``nonnull`` Pointers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1335
msgid ""
"C++ functions that return pointers generate TS definitions with "
"``<SomeClass> | null`` to allow ``nullptr`` by default. If the C++ function "
"is guaranteed to return a valid object, then a policy parameter of "
"``nonnull<ret_val>()`` can be added to the function binding to omit ``| "
"null`` from TS. This avoids having to handle the ``null`` case in TS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1342
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1344
msgid ""
"At time of writing there has been no *comprehensive* *embind* performance "
"testing, either against standard benchmarks, or relative to :ref:`WebIDL-"
"Binder`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/connecting_cpp_and_javascript/embind.rst:1348
msgid ""
"The call overhead for simple functions has been measured at about 200 ns. "
"While there is room for further optimisation, so far its performance in real-"
"world applications has proved to be more than acceptable."
msgstr ""
